---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Quick Start - AutoMem">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a
        href="/docs"
        class="text-automem-primary hover:underline mb-4 inline-block"
        >← Back to Documentation</a
      >

      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
        <span class="gradient-text">Quick Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-12">
        Get AutoMem running in under 5 minutes
      </p>

      <!-- Step 1: Deploy -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Step 1: Deploy AutoMem</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Click the button below to deploy AutoMem to Railway. You'll need a
          Railway account (free to sign up).
        </p>

        <a
          href="https://railway.com/deploy/automem-ai-memory-service"
          target="_blank"
          class="inline-block gradient-bg text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition mb-4"
        >
          Deploy to Railway →
        </a>

        <div
          class="bg-yellow-50 dark:bg-yellow-900/20 border-l-4 border-yellow-400 p-4 mb-4"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <strong>Cost:</strong> Railway charges approximately $5/month for
            AutoMem (includes FalkorDB + memory API service). Qdrant Cloud
            offers a free tier for the vector database.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">What Railway Will Set Up:</h3>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 space-y-2"
          >
            <li>FalkorDB instance (graph database)</li>
            <li>AutoMem API service with automatic health checks</li>
            <li>SSL certificate for secure connections</li>
            <li>
              Environment variables pre-configured (you'll add Qdrant
              credentials in Step 3)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-4">
            <strong>Note:</strong> You should see exactly 2 services in Railway:
            <code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
              >memory-service</code
            >
            and
            <code class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded"
              >falkordb</code
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 2: Get Credentials -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Step 2: Get Your Credentials</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          After deployment completes:
        </p>

        <ol
          class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
        >
          <li>Go to your Railway project dashboard</li>
          <li>Click on the <strong>memory-service</strong> service</li>
          <li>Go to the <strong>Variables</strong> tab</li>
          <li>
            Find and copy these values:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>
                <code
                  class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >AUTOMEM_API_KEY</code
                >
              </li>
              <li>
                <code
                  class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >OPENAI_API_KEY</code
                >
                (you'll set this)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Note your AutoMem endpoint URL (shown in the Settings tab)</li>
        </ol>

        <div
          class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-4 mt-4"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Your endpoint URL will look like
            <code>https://memory-service-production-XXXX.up.railway.app</code>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 3: Set up Qdrant Cloud -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Step 3: Set up Qdrant Cloud</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Qdrant is the vector database that powers AutoMem's semantic search.
          It's hosted separately on Qdrant Cloud's free tier.
        </p>

        <ol
          class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
        >
          <li>
            <strong>Create a free Qdrant Cloud account:</strong>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>
                Go to
                <a
                  href="https://cloud.qdrant.io/"
                  target="_blank"
                  class="text-automem-primary hover:underline"
                  >https://cloud.qdrant.io/</a
                >
              </li>
              <li>Sign up (it's free, no credit card required)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Create a cluster:</strong>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>Click "Create Cluster"</li>
              <li>
                Choose the <strong>Free tier</strong> (1GB storage, perfect for
                personal use)
              </li>
              <li>Select a region close to your Railway deployment</li>
              <li>Wait for the cluster to be provisioned (~2 minutes)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Get your credentials:</strong>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>Click on your cluster name</li>
              <li>
                Copy the <strong>Cluster URL</strong> (looks like
                <code
                  class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >https://xxxxx-xxxxx.aws.cloud.qdrant.io:6333</code
                >)
              </li>
              <li>Copy the <strong>API Key</strong> from the "Access" tab</li>
            </ul>
          </li>

          <li>
            <strong>Add credentials to Railway:</strong>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>Go back to your Railway project</li>
              <li>Click on the <strong>memory-service</strong></li>
              <li>Go to <strong>Variables</strong> tab</li>
              <li>
                Add these two variables:
                <div
                  class="bg-gray-900 text-green-400 p-3 rounded-lg mt-2 text-sm"
                >
                  <div>
                    QDRANT_URL=https://xxxxx-xxxxx.aws.cloud.qdrant.io:6333
                  </div>
                  <div>QDRANT_API_KEY=your-api-key-here</div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                The service will automatically restart with the new
                configuration
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div
          class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 border-l-4 border-green-400 p-4 mt-6"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <strong>Success!</strong> Your AutoMem service is now connected to
            both FalkorDB (graph) and Qdrant (vector) databases.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 4: Configure MCP Client -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">
          Step 4: Configure Your MCP Client
        </h2>

        <div class="mb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
            Choose your AI assistant:
          </p>

          <!-- Claude Desktop -->
          <details class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-lg">
              Claude Desktop Configuration
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                Edit
                <code
                  class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >~/Library/Application
                  Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code
                >
              </p>
              <pre
                class="bg-gray-900 text-green-400 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto text-sm"
              ><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "automem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@verygoodplugins/mcp-automem@latest"
      ],
      "env": {
        "AUTOMEM_ENDPOINT": "https://your-railway-url.up.railway.app",
        "AUTOMEM_API_KEY": "your-api-key-here"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
                Replace <code>your-railway-url</code> and
                <code>your-api-key-here</code> with your actual values. Then
                restart Claude Desktop.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <!-- Cursor -->
          <details class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-4">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-lg">
              Cursor IDE Configuration
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
              <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
                <a
                  href="https://cursor.com/en-US/install-mcp?name=automem&config=eyJlbnYiOnsiQVVUT01FTV9FTkRQT0lOVCI6Imh0dHBzOi8veW91ci1yYWlsd2F5LXVybC51cC5yYWlsd2F5LmFwcCIsIkFVVE9NRU1fQVBJX0tFWSI6InlvdXItYXBpLWtleS1oZXJlIn0sImNvbW1hbmQiOiJucHggLXkgQHZlcnlnb29kcGx1Z2lucy9tY3AtYXV0b21lbUBsYXRlc3QifQ%3D%3D"
                  ><img
                    src="https://cursor.com/deeplink/mcp-install-dark.svg"
                    alt="Add Automem MCP server to Cursor"
                    height="32"
                /></a>
                Alternatively, add to
                <code
                  class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >~/.cursor/mcp.json</code
                >
              </p>
              <pre
                class="bg-gray-900 text-green-400 p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto text-sm"
              ><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "automem": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@verygoodplugins/mcp-automem@latest"
      ],
      "env": {
        "AUTOMEM_ENDPOINT": "https://your-railway-url.up.railway.app",
        "AUTOMEM_API_KEY": "your-api-key-here"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
                Replace the placeholders and restart Cursor. The MCP tools will
                appear in the tools panel.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Step 5: Test -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Step 5: Test It Out</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Try these commands in your AI assistant:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Store a memory:</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 italic">
              "Remember that I prefer TypeScript over JavaScript for new
              projects"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Recall memories:</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 italic">
              "What programming language should I use for my new project?"
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-4">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Check memory health:</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 italic">
              "Check the status of my AutoMem service"
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 border-l-4 border-green-400 p-4 mt-6"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <strong>Success!</strong> Your AI now has persistent memory across
            all devices and conversations. Memories are automatically synced and
            available everywhere.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Troubleshooting -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Troubleshooting</h2>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold">
              I only see 2 services in Railway, where's Qdrant?
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <p>
                <strong>This is correct!</strong> Qdrant is hosted separately on
                Qdrant Cloud, not on Railway. You should see exactly 2 services:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li>
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >memory-service</code
                  >
                  - The AutoMem API
                </li>
                <li>
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >falkordb</code
                  >
                  - The graph database
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">
                Make sure you completed Step 3 to set up Qdrant Cloud and add
                the credentials to Railway.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold">
              Health check is failing
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <p>Check that all environment variables are set correctly:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li>
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >QDRANT_URL</code
                  >
                  - Should include the full URL with port (e.g.,
                  <code>https://xxxxx.cloud.qdrant.io:6333</code>)
                </li>
                <li>
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >QDRANT_API_KEY</code
                  >
                  - Your Qdrant cluster API key
                </li>
                <li>
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >FALKORDB_URL</code
                  >
                  - Auto-configured by Railway
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-2">
                After updating variables, wait 1-2 minutes for the service to
                restart.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
            <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold">
              MCP tools not appearing in Claude/Cursor
            </summary>
            <div class="mt-3 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <p>Try these steps:</p>
              <ol class="list-decimal list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-1">
                <li>
                  Verify your
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >AUTOMEM_ENDPOINT</code
                  >
                  doesn't have a trailing slash
                </li>
                <li>
                  Check that
                  <code
                    class="bg-gray-200 dark:bg-gray-700 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                    >AUTOMEM_API_KEY</code
                  >
                  is copied correctly (no extra spaces)
                </li>
                <li>
                  Restart Claude Desktop or Cursor completely (not just reload)
                </li>
                <li>Check the MCP logs for connection errors</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Next Steps -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Next Steps</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <a
            href="/docs/features"
            class="block p-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg hover:shadow-lg transition"
          >
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Explore Features →</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Learn about memory types, knowledge graphs, and advanced
              capabilities
            </p>
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/verygoodplugins/automem"
            target="_blank"
            class="block p-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg hover:shadow-lg transition"
          >
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">View Source Code →</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              Contribute to AutoMem or run it locally for development
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
